\end{equation}

In addition we will make use of Cherednik's \cite{cher} reflection
property. We only need the case of the reflection matrix $K={\bf 1}$.
For all choices of arrows one derives from eqs.~(\ref{2.11}) and (\ref{2.12})
%//{2.15}
\begin{equation}\label{2.15}
\ba{c}
