For all terms of eq.~(\ref{4.1}), except
for that one where $i=1$, the claim follows
from eq.~(\ref{2.11}) and the special Yang-Baxter relation
%//{4.3c}
\beq \label{4.3c}
R_{12}R_{13}(PP^{\Lambda_2})_{23}=(PP^{\Lambda_2})_{23}R_{13}R_{12}
\eeq
which is a consequence of the general Yang-Baxter relation (\ref{2.1})
for $x_{23}=1/q$ and $x_1\to\infty$.
For the remaining term we use the identity
%//{4.3d}
\beq \label{4.3d}
